// Button component with all states
function SubmitButton({ loading, disabled }) {
  return (
    <button
      type="submit"
      disabled={loading || disabled}
      style={{
        opacity: (loading || disabled) ? 0.6 : 1,
        cursor: (loading || disabled) ? 'not-allowed' : 'pointer',
        background: loading ? '#555' : '#7fff7f',
      }}
    >
      {loading ? '⏳ Thinking...' : 'Run tool'}
    </button>
  );
}

// Error display
{error && (
  <div style={{ color: '#ff6b6b', padding: '12px', border: '1px solid #ff6b6b', borderRadius: 8 }}>
    {error}
  </div>
)}
```

States: idle → loading → success / error → idle again

50%+ of web traffic is mobile. Design for the small screen first:

```css
/* Mobile first: base styles are for small screens */
.input-row { flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; }
.submit-btn { width: 100%; }

/* Then expand for larger screens */
@media (min-width: 640px) {
  .input-row { flex-direction: row; }
  .submit-btn { width: auto; }
}
```

### Quick wins for mobile:
- Minimum tap target: 44×44px (Apple's guideline)
- Font size ≥ 16px on inputs (prevents iOS zoom)
- Avoid horizontal scroll
- Test by resizing browser window to 375px wide
